Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 586
S.P. 269 In Senate, February 25, 2025
in Protection from Abuse Orders
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on February 19, 2025. Referred to the Committee
on Judiciary pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator RAFFERTY of York.
Cosponsored by Representative KUHN of Falmouth, Representative SALISBURY of
Westbrook and
Senators: BENNETT of Oxford, PIERCE of Cumberland, Representatives: DODGE of Belfast,
MITCHELL of Cumberland, MURPHY of Scarborough.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 19-A MRSA §4110, sub-§3, ¶E-1 is enacted to read:
3 E-1. Directing the defendant to refrain from knowingly being within a specified
4 distance of the plaintiff or prohibiting the defendant from being present at a specific
5 location;
6 Sec. 2. Effective date. This Act takes effect January 1, 2026.
7 SUMMARY
88 This bill amends the law governing protection from abuse orders to give the court,
99 beginning January 1, 2026, the authority to issue a final protection order directing the
1100 defendant to refrain from knowingly being within a specified distance of the plaintiff or
1111 prohibiting the defendant from being present at a specific location.
